author: Louis Sealey For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Bayern Munich 5-1 Arsenal: This is Arsene Wenger's lowest moment at Emirates, says Martin Keown | Metro News
text:
Louis Sealey for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 15 Feb 2017 10:12 pm Arsenal boss Arsene Wenger (Picture: Getty) 
Martin Keown said Arsenal’s performance in the 5-1 defeat against Bayern Munich was ‘embarrassing’. 
And the former England defender feels this is now Arsene Wenger’s lowest moment in charge of the Gunners. ‘How can Gibbs be captain?!’ Man Utd legend Roy Keane TEARS into Arsenal flops 
The north London side held their own for 45 minutes in Germany but fell apart in the second-half, conceding three goals in 10 minutes as Bayern took full control of the tie. 
Speaking on BT Sport after the game, Keown said: ‘I feel for Wenger. It’s almost embarrassing. They were outclassed, outplayed. 
‘This is his lowest point ever as Arsenal manager. He must be considering his future.’ Arsenal fixtures
